    "d94b5d55-eb15-4cf4-80d0-eaa6ad65a4fc": {
      "type": "content-list",
      "blocks": {
        "template--16177341137065__d94b5d55-eb15-4cf4-80d0-eaa6ad65a4fc-image-3": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "apply_overlay": false,
            "devices": "mobile_desktop",
            "content_position": "underLeft",
            "subheading": "",
            "title": "",
            "description": "<p><strong>Charlotte, what was your reaction when you saw your engagement ring for the first time?</strong></p><p>ABSOLUTELY STOKED!!! It was my dream ring. I was so so excited to see it!  All those hours of scrolling past the same ring multiple times while I was laying on Olli’s lap (making sure he was looking over my shoulder at my phone) paid off. Also saving it to my phone multiple times! I also sent it to my best friend (because who doesn’t). Still love it to this day! </p><p><strong>Beyond the physical aesthetics, can you delve into the sentimental value your NMJ pieces hold for you? Are there particular moments or memories attached to them that stand out?</strong></p><p>Olli proposed in 2018 in Tuscany in Italy with our oldest who was 3 at the time and it was incredibly special. Our 3 year old took the proposal photo and it was just all around the most magical dreamy day. He saved for a while for this ring and hid it for 2 months and then held onto it all throughout Europe until we got to Tuscany where he knew it was my absolute dream location (after my favourite movie) so I was really happy! Our wedding band is also from NMJ and it compliments my ring so well. Our wedding day was a long time coming, we were engaged for 7 years so to finally be married was so incredible and to share the same last name with my husband and kids is really special! </p>",
            "description_mobile": "<p><strong>Charlotte, what was your reaction when you saw your engagement ring for the first time?</strong></p><p>ABSOLUTELY STOKED!!! It was my dream ring. I was so so excited to see it!  All those hours of scrolling past the same ring multiple times while I was laying on Olli’s lap (making sure he was looking over my shoulder at my phone) paid off. Also saving it to my phone multiple times! I also sent it to my best friend (because who doesn’t). Still love it to this day! </p><p><strong>Beyond the physical aesthetics, can you delve into the sentimental value your NMJ pieces hold for you? Are there particular moments or memories attached to them that stand out?</strong></p><p>Olli proposed in 2018 in Tuscany in Italy with our oldest who was 3 at the time and it was incredibly special. Our 3 year old took the proposal photo and it was just all around the most magical dreamy day. He saved for a while for this ring and hid it for 2 months and then held onto it all throughout Europe until we got to Tuscany where he knew it was my absolute dream location (after my favourite movie) so I was really happy! Our wedding band is also from NMJ and it compliments my ring so well. Our wedding day was a long time coming, we were engaged for 7 years so to finally be married was so incredible and to share the same last name with my husband and kids is really special! </p>",
            "colour_style": "dark",
